locality: Yemen: Hadhramout. uppermost Wadi Azid al Jabal, near the villages Taht Tarik and Dabbak (above the projected track to Tarim). rocky, stony SW facing slope. Alt.: 680-750 m. 20.11.2000, Leg.: N. Kilian, S. O. Bahah, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan NK 6942.
Yemen: Al-Mahra. Jabal Fartak between Haswayn and Al Ghaydah, W facing slopes of the summit plateau with the radio station. Alt.: 550-950 m. 26.11.1999, Leg.: N. Kilian & P. Hein NK 6364.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Northern Fartak Mts, dissected table-land near the track W below J. Karmoum (with the disused radio tower). Relevé A27: Rocky slope (incl. 25°) with small rock ledges, dwarf shrub vegetation dominating. Alt.: 600-650 m. 8.10.2001, Leg.: P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. Reisch YP 1080a.
Wadi Dawkah, North foothills of Jabal Qara, Dhofar.
Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jabal Aswad (190 m) 2 km NE of Hami, S and SW facing slopes. Steep S-SW-exp. rocky slopes with sparse vegetation. Alt.: 30-190 m. 25.9.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian & P. Hein YP 401.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. track between Al Ghaida and Hawf, mountain ridge 20 km E of Al Faydami, S/SW- resp. sea-exposed rocky slopes and cliffs, catching the humidity of the monsoon mist. Dense green vegetation with small shrubs and annuals. Alt.: 50-250 m. 26.9.1998, Leg.: P. Hein, S. A. Ghazanfar & N. Kilian PH 4991.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. upper Wadi Hajar, western flank of the Wadi es Siyel 20 km NW of the village Mintaq [map of Wissmann 1939]. Rocky slopes. Alt.: 850 m. 03.11.2000, Leg.: P. Hein, M. Al-Mashjary & N. Kilian PH 7874.
Oman: Oman, Dhofar: Mirbat plain, small wadi and rocks near the track between Mirbat and Sadh, 8 km E of Mirbat, alt. 50 m, 17°01'N, 54°46'E. Alt.: 50 m. 7.10.1998, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 5452.
